notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Extract Transaction CSV
components.description: Reads financial transaction CSV files from the local filesystem and makes the processed data available via XCom for downstream tasks.
inputs: local filesystem CSV files matching pattern /data/transactions/*.csv

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this is the first step of the pipeline.

components.name: Account Type Branch Check
components.description: Analyzes processed transaction data to determine routing: international accounts go to FATCA, domestic accounts go to IRS.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of transaction CSV.

components.name: Generate FATCA Report
components.description: Creates a FATCA XML report for international accounts and pushes the report status via XCom.
inputs: transaction data routed for international accounts (XCom from branch_account_type_check)

upstream_policy.description: Executes only when the branch decision is 'route_to_fatca'.

connections.purpose: send FATCA XML report to regulatory system

components.name: Generate IRS Report
components.description: Creates an IRS Form 1099 report for domestic accounts and pushes the report status via XCom.
inputs: transaction data routed for domestic accounts (XCom from branch_account_type_check)

upstream_policy.description: Executes only when the branch decision is 'route_to_irs'.

connections.purpose: send IRS 1099 report to regulatory system

components.name: Archive Regulatory Reports
components.description: Merges FATCA and IRS reports, compresses them, and stores the archive in a secure location for compliance retention.
inputs: FATCA XML report file (XCom from generate_fatca_report)
outputs: Compressed archive containing all regulatory reports

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both FATCA and IRS report generation tasks have completed, regardless of their success status.

connections.purpose: store compressed archive of regulatory reports

sources: Financial transaction CSV files stored on the local filesystem
